  "body": "We have been using a hook for our helm chart to perform some key tasks when installing / upgrading a release. Up to version 2.14, calling `helm upgrade --install ...` without the `--wait` flag the behavior was the following:\r\n\r\n- Wait for the job to complete\r\n- If the job fails, return an exit code indicating an error\r\n\r\nNow with version 2.15.1, the same command gives the following behavior:\r\n\r\n- Return right away\r\n- The exit code is a success, even if the job failed.\r\n\r\nThis is particularly relevant when running from a CI tool, as broken releases are wrongly passing. \r\n\r\nOutput of `helm version`:\r\n```\r\nClient: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.15.1\", GitCommit:\"cf1de4f8ba70eded310918a8af3a96bfe8e7683b\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\nServer: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.15.1\", GitCommit:\"cf1de4f8ba70eded310918a8af3a96bfe8e7683b\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\n```\r\nOutput of `kubectl version`:\r\n```\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"16\", GitVersion:\"v1.16.2\", GitCommit:\"c97fe5036ef3df2967d086711e6c0c405941e14b\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2019-10-15T19:18:23Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.12.10\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"14+\", GitVersion:\"v1.14.6-gke.1\", GitCommit:\"61c30f98599ad5309185df308962054d9670bafa\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2019-08-28T11:06:42Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.12.9b4\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n```\r\nCloud Provider/Platform (AKS, GKE, Minikube etc.): GKE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
